I have some close friends that are enchanters (most enchanters I have encountered, however, are sniveling whiners) that are great folks.  I am always happy to see them do well.  I know for sure, if I'm online and they are soloing for crazy exp, I would be invited immediately.  If I could do that, they know they would be with me and zenbober advancing along the exp path.  I really couldn't care less about some enchanters soloing for an aa every 20 minutes.  Fine.  Go for it.  One less unsocial that I have to deal with in or around my guild.<br>
<br>
In an RP capacity, I would like to see us mages as true masters of elements.  Meaning we should command them at will in any zone and any level.  In the current game design, that doesn't make a lot of sense.  However, if they leave the enchanter charm as it is, then maybe we will get to be the true masters of the elements in the future.  I doubt it but its something to hope for.<br>
<br>
In a game design capacity, I always felt that either all classes should be able to solo at some given level much lower than a group capability but still benefit.  Or no classes should solo.  Other than that, all discussion on the matter is moot.  It's based entirely on how a particular class engineer feels about what he/she is working on.<br>
<br>
I can feel that charm nerf coming.  They are going to get slammed.  I don't particularly want it to happen.  I find that quibbling over casting times of spells between classes is just insanely idiotic when so many more important areas need to be addressed.  Let them have their charm and nerf ours.  But atleast consider letting us really be the masters of the elements (and not just 3 of the 4).<br>
<br>
One poster on here stated that there is nothing left to nerf on mages.  We have reached the bottom so go for it.  I couldn't agree more.  Removing our charm/mez that is only used at the end-game in 2 zones is meaningless.  Go for it.  Have fun and I hope you feel better about yourself.  <br>
<br>
Nothing like kicking a mage when he's down huh?  Must feel pretty good to ask for a nerf of a class that's been blasted with them since Kunark.<br>
<br>
But... we are used to it by now.... arn't we? <p><p><br>
